# disambiguation(with:)

**Type Method**

Creates an object whose resolution requires the user to select from among the specified objects.

## Declaration

```swift
class func disambiguation(with stringsToDisambiguate: [INSpeakableString]) -> Self
```

## Parameters

- **stringsToDisambiguate**: An array of [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INSpeakableString] objects for the user to choose from.

## Return Value

A new [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INSpeakableStringResolutionResult] object.

## Discussion

Use this method to create a result object when there is more one value that might match the given parameter. The user is asked to select from among the objects you provide.

## Creating a Resolution Result Object

- **success(with:)**: Creates an object whose resolution involves the successful matching of the specified parameter.
- **confirmationRequired(with:)**: Creates an object whose resolution requires that the user must confirm the value before proceeding.
